        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 3:28PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 327 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Port Hope, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Port Hope, Grindstone City, Redman, and Huron City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
